Topic
Pub/Sub triggered Cloud Function with conditional message routing.
Objective
Build a Pub/Sub → Cloud Function pipeline where the function reacts differently based on message content.
Key Concepts

Eventarc sits between Pub/Sub and the function — not a direct push
Messages arrive base64 encoded — always decode first
if/elif/else logic routes different message types to different actions
--no-allow-unauthenticated not used on event triggers — flag doesn't exist for them
Runtime SA needs roles/run.invoker on the underlying Cloud Run service
Eventarc retries delivery if invocation fails — fix the permission, queued messages will deliver
2nd Gen function logs appear under Cloud Run resource type in Cloud Logging

Practical Work Completed

Created Pub/Sub topic beer
Deployed 2nd Gen Cloud Function with --trigger-topic
Granted runtime SA roles/run.invoker
Published 4 messages: order, restock, close, whisky
Verified each message routed to correct action in logs
Unknown message (whisky) correctly caught by else branch
Clean teardown completed

Confusions / Fixes

Initial 403 errors — Eventarc couldn't invoke function, fixed by granting run.invoker
Eventarc retried queued messages automatically once permission was fixed

Mental Model
One topic, one function, many message types. Each message drives a different action. Same pattern used in billing alerts, pipeline triggers, and notifications.
Plain English Summary
Built a Pub/Sub triggered function that reacted differently depending on the message content. Four messages published, four different responses logged. Fixed a 403 auth error mid-lab by granting the correct invoker role. Clean and working end to end.


